# automaton

Creates deterministic finite automata from description.
The resulting dfa 
1. can be tested on the command line
2. can be turned into a .dot (graphviz) file

## Usage

$ java -jar dfa-conv.jar [optional flags]

### Create a dot file

1. Create an automaton file:
    example.clj

2. Start the converter with the -dot flag:
    $ java -jar dfa-conv.jar -a example.jar -d example.dot

3. Create the dot file (assuming you have graphviz installed):
    $ dot -Tpng -o example.png example.dot

4. Watch and enjoy

### Test your automaton

1. As above

2. Start the converter with the -interactive flag:
    $ java -jar dfa-conv.jar -a example.jar -i

3. Hack the command line

4. Your sequence must start with parantheses or brackets

5. Exit with "exit"

